  "texts": [
    "Moreover, the adoption of privacy-preserving technologies, including federated learning and secure multiparty computation, can reduce risks by allowing model training without direct access to raw personal data (Hao et al. 2025a (Hao et al., 2025b)).",
    "Another critical concern is the possibility of misuse in AI-generated sensory experiences.",
    "As AI models become capable of synthesizing flavors and scents, they may be used to manipulate consumer perception in ways that blur the line between innovation and deception.",
    "For instance, AI can generate synthetic flavors that overstimulate taste receptors without contributing to nutritional value.",
    "This may encourage overconsumption of processed or unhealthy foods, contributing to dietary imbalance and public health concerns."
  ],
